{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 00:56:41.448958", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope and intent\n- Objective: Assess end-to-end network health, detect anomalies, localize faulty components, and identify root cause(s).\n- Topology: OSPF-based enterprise with centralized services in 10.200.0.0/24. Hosts obtain IPv4 via DHCP relayed at distribution layer.\n\nKey observations and evidence\n1) Access hosts lack IPv4 configuration\n- host_1_1_1_1:\n  - Interface state: eth0 UP, but no IPv4 address and no routes.\n  - ip addr/ifconfig: no inet on eth0; ip route is empty.\n- host_2_1_1_1:\n  - Interface state: eth0 UP, but no IPv4 address and no routes.\n  - ip addr/ifconfig: no inet on eth0; ip route is empty.\n- Impact: These hosts cannot reach any L3 service (DNS, web, etc.), explaining absent/unknown reachability results.\n\n2) DHCP server not serving leases\n- dhcp_server (10.200.0.8/24):\n  - netstat -ulnp: No UDP/67 (DHCP server) listener observed. Only 127.0.0.11 UDP is present (container DNS stub).\n  - systemctl status dnsmasq: no output (service appears absent or not running).\n- This indicates the central DHCP service is not active on the DHCP server.\n\n3) Relay path and routing to the DHCP server are healthy\n- router_dist_1_1:\n  - Can ping DHCP server 10.200.0.8 with low latency (1.1–1.2 ms), 0% loss.\n  - Has SVI br0 with 10.1.1.1/24 (gateway to the 10.1.1.0/24 host subnet).\n  - OSPF routes present for 10.200.0.0/24 and other site subnets via 172.16.0.6/31.\n- server_access_router:\n  - Shows 10.200.0.0/24 directly connected and OSPF-learned routes to campus subnets.\n- Conclusion: L3 connectivity between host VLANs and the server farm is intact; the DHCP relay-to-server path is not the blocking point.\n\n4) Core infrastructure and application services appear up\n- DNS server (10.200.0.2/24):\n  - netstat: 53/TCP listeners active (multiple binds). Routing and interface are correct.\n- Web servers:\n  - web_server_0–3: TCP/80 listening (python http server).\n  - load_balancer (10.200.0.7): nginx master process listening on TCP/80.\n- OSPF control-plane:\n  - Both distribution and server access routers have consistent OSPF routes across the enterprise subnets.\n- Implication: Once hosts have IPs, they should be able to route to services.\n\nDetected anomalies\n- Primary anomaly: End hosts do not obtain IPv4 addresses via DHCP (both in distinct access domains: 10.1.1.x and 10.2.1.x).\n- Service anomaly: No active DHCP daemon on dhcp_server (no UDP/67 listener and no running dnsmasq or equivalent service detected).\n\nLocalization\n- Fault domain: Central DHCP server (dhcp_server) and DHCP function.\n- Evidence indicates:\n  - Access switches and distribution SVIs are up (host links are UP; dist br0 has correct subnet).\n  - OSPF routing is correct and path to the server farm (including DHCP server) is reachable.\n  - The absence of a DHCP server process on dhcp_server is systemic and explains failures observed across multiple access blocks.\n\nRoot cause\n- The DHCP service on the central DHCP server is not running (or not installed/configured), resulting in no DHCP offers. Consequently, hosts are not receiving IP addresses, gateways, or DNS settings, and cannot reach any L3 services.\n\nAdditional notes\n- The inventory “hosts” map indicates various host IPs, but these do not reflect the actual state for host_1_1_1_1 and host_2_1_1_1, which currently have no IPv4. The map likely reflects intended or prior assignments.\n- Backend web servers being “not directly accessible” could not be validated from hosts due to lack of IP configuration; however, service listeners are present in the server farm and routing is in place.\n\nOverall network health assessment\n- Routing/OSPF core: Healthy.\n- Server farm services (DNS, web, load balancer): Listening and reachable from routing perspective.\n- Access-layer user experience: Broken due to DHCP failure; hosts cannot join the IP network.\n\nEnd of report (no remediation steps included by request).", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 35347, "output_tokens": 3373, "total_tokens": 38720, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 33664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2368}}}
